NUMBER 2701
NAME Crimson Band, Great Hall
*DESCRIPTION_START
The Great Hall of the citadel is the center of many a merry banquet and
celebration. A long oak table runs the length of the room, while smaller
private tables for members of the Crimson Band and honored guests stand off to
the side. There is an enormous marble fireplace in the western wall with long
silken tapestries to both sides. Tempting kitchen smells waft in through an
arch to the east. To the south is an ornate hallway, on either side of which
stand two guards in randar plate armor.
