ITEM 1 342 ADJ1=984 ADJ2=169

NUMBER 2704
NAME Crimson Band, Cellar
*DESCRIPTION_START
You descend from the west into in an irregularly shaped rectangular cellar
which is cool and damp. It is clear that this room was hewn from the bedrock
below the City. Upon the northern wall stands an immense wine rack containing
an assortment of dust covered wine bottles. Upon the east and south walls are
stacked dozens of aging barrels of ale, port, mead and grog. Prominent among
them is a large oaken keg bearing the label "XXX". A tray of clean mugs
rests on a small pedestal beside the keg.
*DESCRIPTION_END
