NAME Crimson Band, Passageway
*DESCRIPTION_START
This rough hewn passage gradually descends northward for some distance before
it abruptly ends. As in the cellar before it, the rough hewn walls are damp to
the touch. The dust and cobwebs are largely undisturbed, suggesting that this
passage has not been entered for some time.
