ITEM 0 250
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The finely woven silk tapestry depicts a regal ceremony. In the background,
various flags and banners flutter above the Royal Palace. On either side of
Park Avenue, members of the Crimson Band stand at attention in honor of the
soon-to-be King Frederick I. In the foreground, Frederick Kentarus faces the
palace, dressed in flowing white robes and wielding a heavy bejeweled
randar sword. To his left stands the then Guildmaster of the Crimson Band,
wearing a silver tunic bearing the image of a fierce crimson eagle.
*DESCRIPTION_END
