NUMBER 2714
NAME Crimson Band, Barracks
*DESCRIPTION_START
This large spartan room is the sleeping area for the guards and servants of
the Crimson Band. Cots and chests containing personal effects are laid out in
neat rows with military precision. The room is divided into three sub-areas
which are designated according to morning, afternoon or evening watch. Inset
into the north wall is a titanium door leading to the armory. A short hall
in the east wall bends to the south, ending in a gleaming metal door. The last
door in this room is made of plain wood and is inset into the south wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
