NUMBER 2717
NAME Citadel, Guildmaster's Office
*DESCRIPTION_START
The walls of the office are the exposed blocks stone which make up most of the
citadel. Bookcases line the western and southern walls, while the wall to the
east is pierced by a tall, narrow, window. Covering most of the north wall is
a large tapestry. Below it is the doorway and a sturdy wooden cabinet,
reinforced with iron. The room is dominated by a large c-shaped desk, sturdily
crafted from fine oak. A straight-backed oak chair sits inside the "C" and a
few other, more comfortable-looking chairs face it from outside the arc. The
gleaming metal door in the west wall leads back to the barracks.
*DESCRIPTION_END
