NUMBER 2722
NAME Crimson Band, Arena
;CHANNEL 1765
ECHOCHAN 1765
*DESCRIPTION_START
During the day the sun streams into this large, oval arena. At night it is lit
by torches scattered around the walls. The floor, stained with the blood of
past combatants, is composed of packed gravel which provides excellent footing.
A marble statue faces you from the western end of the arena. Next to the statue
is a rusty iron gate. A ramp leads up to the waiting area for the combatants
and a set of iron double doors leads out of the arena. To the south is a
balcony upon which are rows of wood chairs.
*DESCRIPTION_END
