NUMBER 2724
NAME Crimson Band, Sergeant's Office
*DESCRIPTION_START
The first thing you notice upon entering the office of the Sergeant at Arms is
a massive silk screen painting hanging on the north wall below which rests a
simple but comfortable fouton. A red flag with battle streamers attached to
the top occupies a corner beside an uquart bookcase filled with treatises and
drawings pertaining to weapons and fighting styles. In the corner opposite the
flag stands a magically preserved skrag, posed with its trident in an attack
position. Three uquart chairs, upholstered in firetiger skins and arranged so
that two face one, sit in the center of the room.
*DESCRIPTION_END
